      • getSecondTypeIndex

        int getSecondTypeIndex()
        Return the index of starting second type. The result of |pNum / pType| is round-down. To be precise, Java refers to this as rounding toward zero.
        Returns:
        the index of starting second type.

      • getThirdTypeIndex

        int getThirdTypeIndex()
        Return the index of starting third type. Return |pNum| when pType is 2. In the case 3, Ex. n=4 : {0}, {1}, {2, 3} => return 2 Ex. n=5 : {0}, {1, 2}, {3, 4} => return 3 Ex. n=6 : {0, 1}, {2, 3}, {4, 5} => return 4
        Returns:
        the index of starting third type.
